headline: Advanced Micro Devices (NasdaqGS:AMD) Rises 10% In One Week
summary: Advanced Micro Devices (NasdaqGS:AMD) announced its next-generation EPYC processor, Venice, leveraging TSMC's advanced 2nm technology, alongside the successful launch of its 5th Gen EPYC processors for Oracle Cloud Infrastructure. These developments underscore the company's commitment to innovation and partnerships, possibly impacting its 10% share price increase over the past week. While these announcements support AMD's technological advancement, the broader market also rose by nearly 5%...
